<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6636> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6636" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/3> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Author of a law providing for IIII viri among the magistrates of Petelia (CIL 10.113, 114-ILS 6468, 6469). Niccolini (FTP 428) suggests a date before the Social War, but Rudolph (Stadt und Staat im alten Italien 94f., 118, note) follows Hardy in attributing it to Cinna in 87 (Some Problems of Roman History 286ff.). No title preserved." .
